<TITLE> Italy police arrest dozens in new Mafia crackdown </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 PALERMO, Dec 4 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Italian police on Tuesday arrested dozens of Mafia suspects in Sicily, the latest in a series of roundups that the government said were crippling the organised crime group. "We're exerting a state presence in Sicily that is changing the climate there and eradicating the clans," said Interior Minister Giuliano Amato. Police said they were executing 70 arrest orders, including one for Enzo Santapaola, the son of an infamous mob boss in the Sicilian city of Catania, Benedetto "Nitto" Santapaola. The suspects are accused of extortion, drug trafficking and other crimes. The operation follows a series of high-profile sweeps targeting the Sicilian Mafia, including last month's arrest of "boss of bosses" Salvatore Lo Piccolo after nearly a quarter century on the run. Magistrates believe Lo Piccolo assumed command of the Cosa Nostra following the capture in 2006 of Bernardo Provenzano. Another important Mafia leader, who was one of Italy's 30-most wanted men, was shot and killed by police on Monday as he tried to escape arre
